description: Russia-Ukraine War Highlights: US President Joe Biden, Secretary of State Antony Blinken, Canada Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and other top Canadian government officials have been barred from entering Russia by the Kremlin. At least five people were killed in Kyiv after a series of Russian airstrikes hit a residential neighbourhood in the Ukrainian capital, igniting a huge fire and a frantic rescue effort in a 15-story apartment building. At least five people were killed. Shockwaves from an explosion also damaged the entry to a downtown subway station that has been used as a bomb shelter. City authorities tweeted an image of the blown-out facade, saying trains would no longer stop at the station. Meanwhile, Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said his country will no longer look to join the NATO -- one of Russia's "conditions" -- and made an impassioned plea to the Canadian parliament for aid and support. Meanwhile, the Russian offensive in Ukraine edged closer to central Kyiv even as the two countries kept open a narrow diplomatic channel with more planned talks.
